Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Squeeze the @Steamed Basmati Rice{1%pouch} to separate the grains. Tear a strip
approx 2cm along the top. Cook the rice according to pack instructions.

While the rice cooks, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated)
(or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the @Sea Bass Fillets{2} into a #medium bowl{} with the @Olive Oil{3/4%tbsp}
for the marinade and the @Curry Powder Mix{1%sachet}.

Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}, then mix well to coat the fish.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Lay the sea bass, skin-side down, onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Bake the fish on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the garlic, @Tomato Puree{30%g} and @Tikka Masala Paste{75%g}.
Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @Creme Fraiche{75%g}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{200%ml} for the sauce,
into the spices. Simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the sauce a handful at a time until wilted and
piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}, then remove from the
heat. Add a splash of water if the sauce is a little thick.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between
your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the curry sauce and top with the fish.

Enjoy!